WEBVTT

00:01.101 --> 00:03.370
<i>PREVIOUSLY</i>
<i>ON "WAYWARD PINES"...</i>

00:03.370 --> 00:04.705
EVERYBODY'S
A PRISONER HERE.

00:04.705 --> 00:07.074
THERE'S CAMERAS
AND MIKES EVERYWHERE.

00:07.074 --> 00:09.042
THIS WHOLE TOWN
IS UNDER SURVEILLANCE.

00:09.042 --> 00:10.277
Brad: THE THING
ABOUT THIS TOWN IS THAT

00:10.277 --> 00:11.678
THEY FOCUS
ON THE CHILDREN.

00:11.678 --> 00:14.715
IT'S ALL ABOUT SHAPING
THE MIND OF THE CHILD.

00:14.715 --> 00:17.251
GUESS WHAT?
I'M GONNA BE YOUR TEACHER.

00:17.251 --> 00:19.219
Ben: HAVE YOU EVER
BEEN TO THAT FENCE?

00:19.219 --> 00:22.523
DO YOU KNOW ABOUT THOSE...
ANIMALS ON THE OTHER SIDE?

00:22.523 --> 00:24.157
BEN!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

00:24.157 --> 00:26.293
I TOLD YOU I WAS GOING
TO PICK YOU UP AT SCHOOL!

00:26.293 --> 00:29.429
MR. BURKE, SO THRILLED
TO HAVE YOU AS OUR NEW SHERIFF.

00:29.429 --> 00:32.132
Ethan: I GUESS WHEN YOU
KILL SOMEBODY IN THIS TOWN,

00:32.132 --> 00:33.500
THEY GIVE YOU HIS JOB.

00:33.500 --> 00:35.469
WHY WON'T YOUR PARENTS
TAKE YOU HOME, BEN?

00:35.469 --> 00:37.070
'CAUSE THEY CAN'T.

00:37.070 --> 00:40.374
I WILL DO EVERYTHING
IN MY POWER TO ENSURE

00:40.374 --> 00:42.576
THAT THE EVILS OF THIS TOWN
ARE BROUGHT TO LIGHT.

00:42.576 --> 00:44.444
WHY CAN'T ANYBODY
LEAVE THIS TOWN?

00:44.444 --> 00:46.280
THERE'S ONLY
ONE WAY OUT.

00:48.515 --> 00:50.350
Theresa:
"THERESA, CONGRATULATIONS!

00:50.350 --> 00:54.121
"A SPOT HAS JUST OPENED AT
WAYWARD PINES REALTY ASSOCIATES.

00:54.121 --> 00:56.757
"ONE OF OUR SENIOR REALTORS
HAS CHOSEN TO RETIRE.

00:56.757 --> 00:59.026
I NEED YOU TO STAY HERE.

00:59.026 --> 01:00.227
I'M GOING TO BOISE
TO GET SOME HELP.

01:06.033 --> 01:08.035
[ GROWLING ]

01:10.237 --> 01:12.372
[ GASPS ]

01:13.273 --> 01:15.709
[ GRUNTS ]

01:15.709 --> 01:17.711
[ PANTING ]

01:50.477 --> 01:51.979
[ RUSTLING ]

01:59.753 --> 02:01.088
[ GASPS ]

02:01.088 --> 02:03.056
[ PANTING ]

02:03.056 --> 02:05.759
[ GROANING ]

02:05.759 --> 02:07.027
[ RAPID FOOTSTEPS ]

02:10.063 --> 02:11.264
[ GROWLING ]

02:12.666 --> 02:14.735
[ SCREECHING ]

03:00.580 --> 03:05.185
HEY, SO TOMORROW,
DO YOU WANT TO WALK TO SCHOOL

03:05.185 --> 03:08.088
WITH SAM AND KATIE
AND ME?

03:08.088 --> 03:11.358
WE ALWAYS GO TOGETHER,
AND YOU LIVE RIGHT BY US, SO...

03:11.358 --> 03:13.360
OH. YEAH, SURE.

03:13.360 --> 03:15.062
COOL.

03:15.062 --> 03:16.496
UH, WHAT TIME?

03:16.496 --> 03:18.999
UH, 7:00.

03:18.999 --> 03:21.568
CORNER OF MAPLE AND 15th.
COOL. SO...

03:25.605 --> 03:29.342
SO, TONIGHT WAS COOL.

03:31.211 --> 03:33.980
SORRY.
I SUCK AT THIS.

03:33.980 --> 03:35.682
I COULDN'T TELL.

03:43.190 --> 03:45.358
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:49.296 --> 03:51.298
[ SIGHS ]

03:53.033 --> 03:55.168
[ WATER RUNNING ]

03:57.204 --> 03:59.639
MOM.

03:59.639 --> 04:00.974
YOU OKAY?

04:00.974 --> 04:03.477
YEAH.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

04:03.477 --> 04:06.012
I'M GOOD.
HOW ARE YOU?

04:06.012 --> 04:07.547
WHERE'S DAD?

04:07.547 --> 04:09.116
HE'S WORKING LATE.

04:12.552 --> 04:15.422
HE'S TRYING TO FINISH UP
THIS CASE, BUT HE'S CLOSE.

04:15.422 --> 04:17.557
AND WE'RE GONNA
GET OUT OF HERE SOON

04:17.557 --> 04:19.059
AND GET BACK TO SEATTLE.

04:20.260 --> 04:22.529
[ GROANING ]

04:24.030 --> 04:25.398
OW, OW.

04:25.398 --> 04:26.967
HOW DOES THAT SOUND?

04:28.268 --> 04:29.569
GREAT.

04:37.477 --> 04:39.746
[ SIGHS ]

04:39.746 --> 04:42.716
[ PANTING, GROANING ]

04:50.724 --> 04:53.360
[ BIRD CRIES ]

05:13.380 --> 05:15.515
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

05:24.057 --> 05:25.592
MORNING.

05:25.592 --> 05:28.028
HMM.
WHAT'S THE RUSH?

05:28.028 --> 05:29.329
I TOLD AMY
I'D WALK TO SCHOOL

05:29.329 --> 05:31.064
WITH HER AND
A COUPLE FRIENDS, SO...

05:31.064 --> 05:33.433
BEN, I THOUGHT WE TALKED
ABOUT THIS ALREADY.

05:33.433 --> 05:36.303
I WANT TO WALK YOU
TO SCHOOL EVERY DAY.

05:36.303 --> 05:38.405
IT'S A FIVE-MINUTE WALK.
I THINK I'LL SURVIVE.

05:38.405 --> 05:41.241
BEN.
LOOK, THEY'RE
MY FRIENDS, MOM.

05:46.079 --> 05:48.481
LISTEN, I KNOW
THAT THEY'RE YOUR FRIENDS.

05:48.481 --> 05:50.283
I'M JUST TELLING YOU

05:50.283 --> 05:51.651
THAT WE DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHAT THIS TOWN IS ABOUT YET

05:51.651 --> 05:54.154
AND THAT MAYBE
WE SHOULD BE EXTRA CAREFUL

05:54.154 --> 05:55.422
'CAUSE
WE ALSO DON'T KNOW

05:55.422 --> 05:58.058
WHO OUR REAL FRIENDS
ARE YET, OKAY?

05:58.058 --> 05:59.226
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

05:59.226 --> 06:01.761
WHO WOULD EVER
WANT TO BE FRIENDS

06:01.761 --> 06:04.497
WITH A LOSER LIKE ME,
RIGHT?

06:04.497 --> 06:07.167
BEN. BEN,
I DID NOT MEAN THAT.

06:07.167 --> 06:09.069
YOU AND DAD TOLD ME
THAT I SHOULD FIT IN.

06:09.069 --> 06:12.339
MAYBE THAT'S WEIRD FOR YOU,
BUT <i>I</i> AM.

06:12.339 --> 06:13.573
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

06:13.573 --> 06:15.108
YOU'RE JUST
SITTING AROUND THE HOUSE,

06:15.108 --> 06:17.177
HOPING THAT THINGS
WILL MAGICALLY GET BETTER,

06:17.177 --> 06:19.212
BUT THEY NEVER DO.

06:24.184 --> 06:26.720
[ SIGHS ]

06:26.720 --> 06:28.722
[ SIGHS ]

06:37.330 --> 06:39.199
[ SIGHS ]

06:41.201 --> 06:45.038
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

07:08.161 --> 07:09.462
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

07:09.462 --> 07:10.697
HEADS UP!

07:10.697 --> 07:12.632
Boy: HURRY UP!

07:15.368 --> 07:18.038
HEY, BEN,
HOW'S IT GOING?
HEY.

07:19.572 --> 07:21.207
HEY, BEN.
HEY.

07:21.207 --> 07:25.545
HEY. HEY.
WHAT IS IT?

07:25.545 --> 07:27.681
I --
ALL THESE KIDS...

07:27.681 --> 07:29.115
SEE YOU, BEN.
SEE YA.

07:29.115 --> 07:31.017
BYE.

07:31.017 --> 07:34.554
THEY'RE ALL BEING NICE TO ME
BECAUSE THEY WANT TO BE, RIGHT?

07:34.554 --> 07:36.022
WHAT?

07:36.022 --> 07:38.525
LIKE,
THEY WEREN'T TOLD TO...

07:38.525 --> 07:40.460
I DON'T KNOW --
BE MY FRIEND, WERE THEY?

07:40.460 --> 07:42.662
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

07:44.397 --> 07:48.401
AT MY OLD SCHOOL,
EVERYTHING WAS DIFFERENT

07:48.401 --> 07:50.503
AND EVERYONE
WAS DIFFERENT TOWARDS ME.

07:50.503 --> 07:52.238
IT'S LIKE
THEY DIDN'T EVEN SEE ME.

07:52.238 --> 07:56.176
AND THEN, I COME HERE
FOR A COUPLE DAYS,

07:56.176 --> 07:59.079
AND EVERYONE TALKS TO ME,
EVERYONE SEES ME.

07:59.079 --> 08:01.047
ISN'T THAT
A GOOD THING?

08:01.047 --> 08:02.349
I GUESS.

08:02.349 --> 08:03.483
I-I JUST DON'T
UNDERSTAND

08:03.483 --> 08:05.618
WHY THINGS
ARE SO DIFFERENT HERE.

08:05.618 --> 08:08.755
THIS SCHOOL...

08:08.755 --> 08:13.126
IT ISN'T LIKE YOUR OTHER SCHOOL
OR ANY OTHER SCHOOL.

08:13.126 --> 08:14.627
WE'RE ALL
IN THIS TOGETHER.

08:14.627 --> 08:17.330
[ STAMMERS ]
WAIT, ALL OF WHAT TOGETHER?

08:17.330 --> 08:21.434
Woman: <i>REED FINLEY,</i>
<i>CARRIE BARNES, BENJAMIN BURKE,</i>

08:21.434 --> 08:24.070
<i>PLEASE REPORT TO ROOM ONE</i>
<i>FOR ORIENTATION.</i>

08:24.070 --> 08:25.405
ORIENTAT--
WHAT'S ORIENTATION?

08:25.405 --> 08:27.240
<i>REED FINLEY...</i>

08:27.240 --> 08:30.210
GOOD LUCK.
<i>...CARRIE BARNES,</i>
<i>BENJAMIN BURKE,</i>

08:30.210 --> 08:33.246
<i>PLEASE REPORT TO ROOM ONE</i>
<i>FOR ORIENTATION.</i>

08:35.281 --> 08:37.150
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

08:46.526 --> 08:49.129
[ BELL JINGLES ]

08:49.129 --> 08:51.698
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
HELLO?

08:54.200 --> 08:56.436
[ WOLF-WHISTLES ]

08:56.436 --> 08:59.105
WELL, WELL,
YOU MUST BE THERESA,

08:59.105 --> 09:00.473
MY NEW NUMBER TWO.

09:00.473 --> 09:02.642
EH, THE NAME'S BILL.

09:02.642 --> 09:05.612
BUT EVERYONE HERE, THEY --
THEY CALLS ME "BIG BILL."

09:05.612 --> 09:09.115
WHY? I HAVE NO IDEA.
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:09.115 --> 09:11.117
AH. [ CLICKS TONGUE ]
I GOT TO SAY,

09:11.117 --> 09:13.620
YOU'RE A HELL OF A LOT EASIER
ON THE EYES THAN OLD PETEY.

09:13.620 --> 09:15.055
[ LAUGHS ]

09:15.055 --> 09:17.357
[ CHUCKLES ]
DON'T GET ME WRONG.

09:17.357 --> 09:19.125
PETEY WAS
A GOOD FRIEND,

09:19.125 --> 09:21.528
BUT GRAFFITI
ON MAIN STREET?

09:21.528 --> 09:24.130
YOU JUST NEVER KNOW
ABOUT SOME PEOPLE.

09:24.130 --> 09:28.635
HMM. THIS WAY, HON.
KEEP UP.

09:28.635 --> 09:30.170
IS IT JUST YOU HERE?

09:30.170 --> 09:31.571
WELL, HENRIETTA
HELPS WITH THE BOOKS.

09:31.571 --> 09:34.340
BUT OTHERWISE,
IT'S, UH, JUST ME AND YOU --

09:34.340 --> 09:35.408
PARTNERS.

09:35.408 --> 09:37.077
I'M SORRY
ABOUT ALL THIS MESS.

09:37.077 --> 09:38.678
I ASKED HER TO PUT
ALL THIS AWAY,

09:38.678 --> 09:41.247
BUT THE POOR WOMAN
WAS DISTRAUGHT.

09:41.247 --> 09:43.550
SHE WANTED
PETEY'S JOB HERSELF.

09:43.550 --> 09:45.618
UH, SHE LOST
THE JOB TO ME?

09:45.618 --> 09:47.387
OH, I'M SURE
SHE'S MUCH MORE EXPERIENCED.

09:47.387 --> 09:49.289
THEY TOLD ME YOU WERE
THE PERFECT CHOICE.

09:49.289 --> 09:50.557
YEAH, WHO IS THEY,
EXACTLY?

09:50.557 --> 09:51.558
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'VE BEEN --

09:51.558 --> 09:53.493
HERE WE GO!
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:53.493 --> 09:55.128
YOUR FIRST CLIENT.

10:01.301 --> 10:03.169
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO
DO WITH THIS?

10:03.169 --> 10:04.637
IS THERE A NUMBER
I SHOULD BE CALLING, OR --

10:04.637 --> 10:06.039
OH, NOT ANYMORE.

10:06.039 --> 10:07.340
HE LOST HIS PHONE
IN THE ACCIDENT.

10:07.340 --> 10:08.708
THE ACCIDENT?

10:08.708 --> 10:10.276
WELL, YOU SEE,
WAYNE, HE WORKS --

10:10.276 --> 10:12.178
WELL,
<i>WORKED</i> CONSTRUCTION,

10:12.178 --> 10:15.148
YOU KNOW, SETTING THOSE TRAFFIC
CONES FOR THOSE PAVING PROJECTS.

10:15.148 --> 10:17.117
LATE AT NIGHT,
JUST HIM,

10:17.117 --> 10:19.052
MOVING THOSE TRAFFIC CONES
ALL BY HIS LONESOME,

10:19.052 --> 10:20.687
THEN BOOM!

10:20.687 --> 10:24.357
HE GETS HIT BY A POLICE CAR
AND THROWN RIGHT OVER THE HOOD.

10:24.357 --> 10:26.459
ROLLED OFF THE ROAD [SLAMS HAND]
DOWN A DITCH [SLAMS HAND]

10:26.459 --> 10:29.262
AND CRASHED HEADFIRST
INTO A CONCRETE DAM.

10:29.262 --> 10:30.697
BUT PAM --

10:30.697 --> 10:32.165
YOU KNOW NURSE PAM?
MM-HMM.

10:32.165 --> 10:33.333
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

10:33.333 --> 10:34.701
WELL, SHE FIXED HIM UP
REAL GOOD.

10:34.701 --> 10:36.970
BUT NOW IT'S TIME FOR HIM
TO LEAVE HER CARE.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.972
B-BUT THE PROBLEM IS,
WAYNE, WELL, HE --

10:38.972 --> 10:41.508
WELL, HE LOST DAMN NEAR
EVERYTHING IN THAT ACCIDENT,

10:41.508 --> 10:42.709
MORE THAN HIS PHONE.

10:42.709 --> 10:44.677
HE DOESN'T EVEN HAVE
A PLACE TO STAY.

10:44.677 --> 10:48.281
THAT'S WHERE
YOU COME IN.

10:48.281 --> 10:50.049
OKAY, SO YOU WANT ME
TO SELL HIM A HOUSE?

10:50.049 --> 10:51.284
[ Chuckling ] NO.

10:51.284 --> 10:54.420
I WANT YOU
TO <i>GIVE</i> HIM A HOUSE.

10:54.420 --> 10:56.589
YOU'LL EARN A GOLD STAR
IF YOU DO.

10:56.589 --> 10:58.591
YOU WANT ME
TO <i>GIVE</i> HIM A HOUSE?
MM-HMM.

10:58.591 --> 11:01.461
THINK OF IT AS A --

11:01.461 --> 11:05.198
AS A WELCOMING PRESENT FROM
HIS FRIENDS AT WAYWARD PINES.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.101
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

11:08.101 --> 11:10.970
WE'RE GONNA MAKE
A HELL OF A TEAM.

11:10.970 --> 11:14.340
YOU THANK YOUR HUSBAND
FOR KILLING PETEY, WILL YA?

11:14.340 --> 11:15.441
[ LAUGHS ]

11:37.630 --> 11:40.133
HI, I'M BEN.

11:40.133 --> 11:41.367
CARRIE.

11:41.367 --> 11:42.602
REED.

11:42.602 --> 11:44.237
YOU BOTH NEW HERE,
TOO?

11:47.974 --> 11:49.976
WHAT'S 111?

11:49.976 --> 11:51.644
NO IDEA,
BUT I'M 110.

11:51.644 --> 11:53.046
AND I'M 109.

12:00.553 --> 12:02.255
[ SQUEAKING IN DISTANCE ]

12:15.435 --> 12:16.970
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

12:55.475 --> 12:58.711
WELCOME TO ORIENTATION.

12:58.711 --> 13:00.747
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

13:08.454 --> 13:11.524
[ ZIPPER OPENS ]

13:28.041 --> 13:32.578
THESE ARE STUDENTS
001 THROUGH 003,

13:32.578 --> 13:36.516
THE VERY FIRST
TO COMPLETE ORIENTATION.

13:36.516 --> 13:39.619
WHEN THEY WERE INVITED
TO THIS ROOM,

13:39.619 --> 13:41.587
THEY WERE JUST LIKE YOU,

13:41.587 --> 13:44.023
THEY HAD ONLY JUST ARRIVED
IN WAYWARD PINES.

13:44.023 --> 13:47.293
AND LIKE YOU,
THEY WERE INVITED TO THIS ROOM

13:47.293 --> 13:51.564
BECAUSE THEY SHOWED
GREAT APTITUDE

13:51.564 --> 13:55.735
DURING OUR
INDIVIDUAL SESSIONS.

13:55.735 --> 14:00.073
ASSUMING YOU ALL
MAKE IT THROUGH TODAY...

14:01.708 --> 14:04.043
...YOUR PICTURE
WILL JOIN THESE STUDENTS,

14:04.043 --> 14:07.113
AND YOU WILL
OFFICIALLY BECOME PART

14:07.113 --> 14:11.484
OF THE FIRST GENERATION
OF WAYWARD PINES.

14:15.154 --> 14:19.125
THIS IS A GREAT HONOR
AND PRIVILEGE.

14:19.125 --> 14:24.130
WE ONLY ALLOW THOSE
WHO ARE TRULY EXCEPTIONAL

14:24.130 --> 14:26.666
TO JOIN
THE FIRST GENERATION.

14:26.666 --> 14:31.337
WE ONLY ALLOW THOSE
WHO WE BELIEVE...

14:31.337 --> 14:33.005
ARE TRULY READY.

14:33.005 --> 14:35.074
READY FOR WHAT?

14:35.074 --> 14:37.477
FOR THE TRUTH.

14:45.017 --> 14:46.519
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

15:07.407 --> 15:09.308
MR. JOHNSON?

15:12.245 --> 15:15.248
MY NAME
IS THERESA BURKE,

15:15.248 --> 15:18.117
AND I'M HERE...

15:18.117 --> 15:20.520
BECAUSE I HEARD THAT
YOU NEEDED SOME ASSISTANCE.

15:23.589 --> 15:26.692
IN FINDING A PLACE?

15:29.495 --> 15:31.764
I HAVE A PLACE THAT I THINK
YOU'RE REALLY GONNA LOVE.

15:31.764 --> 15:34.367
IT'S, UM...

15:34.367 --> 15:36.736
IT JUST CAME
ON THE MARKET.
STOP.

15:38.504 --> 15:40.339
PLEASE, JUST STOP.

15:40.339 --> 15:42.642
I'M SORRY,
MR. JOHNSON.

15:42.642 --> 15:44.710
IT MUST BE A VERY
DIFFICULT TIME FOR YOU.

15:44.710 --> 15:46.479
I AM JUST HERE
TO HELP.

15:46.479 --> 15:50.183
I JUST WANT TO
BE ALONE, PLEASE.

15:50.183 --> 15:52.585
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE OKAY?
DO YOU WANT ME TO GET A NURSE?

15:52.585 --> 15:55.188
NO, NOT --

15:55.188 --> 15:57.089
NOT HER.

16:03.429 --> 16:08.134
WAYNE, IF YOU'RE
FEELING CONFUSED AT ALL

16:08.134 --> 16:10.436
OR YOU NEED
SOMEONE TO TALK TO,

16:10.436 --> 16:12.472
YOU CAN TALK TO ME,
OKAY?

16:12.472 --> 16:14.340
I ALSO
WAS IN AN ACCIDENT.

16:18.144 --> 16:20.346
DID YOU SEE IT, TOO?

16:20.346 --> 16:22.415
SEE WHAT?

16:26.486 --> 16:29.589
AFTER THE ACCIDENT...

16:29.589 --> 16:33.326
I SAW SOMETHING.

16:33.326 --> 16:35.361
SOMETHING AWFUL.

16:37.196 --> 16:42.034
THEY DID S-SOMETHING
TO ME, TO US,

16:42.034 --> 16:43.436
AND THAT NURSE,
S-SHE -- SHE WAS THERE.

16:55.014 --> 16:57.617
HEY.

16:57.617 --> 16:59.619
So, who have you
told this to?

16:59.619 --> 17:01.320
NO -- NO ONE.

17:01.320 --> 17:06.359
This place,
this town is not safe.

17:06.359 --> 17:08.594
We need to be very,
very careful.

17:08.594 --> 17:11.664
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

17:13.432 --> 17:16.736
Now tell me what you saw,
quickly.

17:16.736 --> 17:19.705
UH...
WHAT A PLEASANT SURPRISE.

17:19.705 --> 17:22.174
I DIDN'T EXPECT
TO SEE YOU, THERESA.

17:22.174 --> 17:23.709
ARE YOU ACQUAINTED
WITH DEAR MR. JOHNSON?

17:23.709 --> 17:26.512
I WAS ACTUALLY JUST SHOWING HIM
SOME NEW PROPERTIES.

17:26.512 --> 17:29.515
OH, OF COURSE.
YOU GOT PETER'S JOB.

17:29.515 --> 17:31.217
CONGRATULATIONS.

17:31.217 --> 17:33.085
I CERTAINLY HOPE YOU DO
BETTER THAN POOR PETER.

17:33.085 --> 17:36.355
OF COURSE, I KNEW
HE'D NEVER MAKE IT.

17:36.355 --> 17:38.291
FAR TOO MUCH
OF A FREETHINKER.

17:48.501 --> 17:52.104
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I HAVE AN IDEA.

17:52.104 --> 17:53.406
WHAT DO YOU SAY? LET'S TAKE
A LOOK AT THIS HOUSE.

17:53.406 --> 17:54.740
I REALLY THINK
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE IT.

17:54.740 --> 17:58.344
IT HAS A BIG YARD,
IT'S ON A CORNER LOT,

17:58.344 --> 18:01.047
AND IT'S PRIVATE,
VERY PRIVATE.

18:03.516 --> 18:05.651
NOW, TELL ME
WHAT YOU SEE.

18:05.651 --> 18:09.255
UH, IT -- IT LOOKS
LIKE WAYWARD PINES.

18:09.255 --> 18:12.258
CLOSE, BUT NOT QUITE.

18:12.258 --> 18:15.661
THIS PHOTOGRAPH
WAS TAKEN 14 YEARS AGO,

18:15.661 --> 18:19.599
ABOUT 100 YARDS BEYOND
THE PERIMETER OF WAYWARD PINES.

18:19.599 --> 18:20.666
[ PROJECTOR CLICKS ]

18:20.666 --> 18:23.069
NOW TAKE ANOTHER LOOK.

18:23.069 --> 18:26.672
DO YOU SEE ANYTHING OFF
ABOUT THIS PHOTO?

18:26.672 --> 18:30.409
YEAH, THERE'S SOMETHING
IN THE TOP LEFT CORNER.

18:30.409 --> 18:32.278
VERY GOOD, BEN.

18:33.579 --> 18:37.283
THIS WAS OUR FIRST REAL EVIDENCE
OF THEIR EXISTENCE.

18:37.283 --> 18:39.518
UH, WHAT'S EXISTENCE?

18:39.518 --> 18:41.621
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME?

18:41.621 --> 18:44.056
BIGFOOT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:44.056 --> 18:47.126
BIGFOOT IS ALWAYS ALONE,
IS HE NOT?

18:48.427 --> 18:52.431
THE NEXT PHOTOGRAPH
WAS TAKEN THREE MONTHS LATER.

18:52.431 --> 18:56.469
IT COST US
TWO LIVES TO GET.

19:00.206 --> 19:02.108
[ GROWLING IN DISTANCE ]

19:07.380 --> 19:09.015
WHAT ARE THEY?

19:09.015 --> 19:12.251
WE REFER TO THEM
AS ABBIES.

19:12.251 --> 19:15.988
ABBIES?
SHORT FOR ABERRATIONS.

19:15.988 --> 19:21.293
THEY ARE THE RESULT OF
A SERIES OF GENETIC MUTATIONS,

19:21.293 --> 19:22.461
OR ABERRATIONS.

19:25.765 --> 19:28.634
THEY EVOLVED
IN A HARSH ENVIRONMENT

19:28.634 --> 19:31.003
AND ARE NOW THE SINGLE
MOST EFFICIENT CARNIVORES

19:31.003 --> 19:32.371
ON THE PLANET.

19:32.371 --> 19:36.075
IN THE FOOD CHAIN,
NOTHING ELSE COMES CLOSE,

19:36.075 --> 19:38.310
NOT EVEN US.

19:43.582 --> 19:45.418
[ GROWLING ]

19:45.418 --> 19:49.555
ON ITS OWN, AN ABBY CAN KILL
AND DEVOUR AN ARMED SOLDIER

19:49.555 --> 19:51.190
IN A MATTER OF MINUTES.

19:51.190 --> 19:55.594
ISOLATED, IT IS POSSIBLE,
ALBEIT UNLIKELY,

19:55.594 --> 19:57.329
TO OVERCOME AN ABBY,

19:57.329 --> 20:00.366
BUT THEY ALWAYS
TRAVEL IN HERDS.

20:02.368 --> 20:06.138
AND IF YOU COME ACROSS A HERD,
SURVIVAL IS,

20:06.138 --> 20:08.607
QUITE SIMPLY, IMPOSSIBLE.

20:11.177 --> 20:13.345
NOTE THE BIRD-LIKE TALONS,

20:13.345 --> 20:17.717
CAPABLE OF KILLING PREY
IN A SINGLE STROKE.

20:19.752 --> 20:22.588
THEIR EARS HAVE
AN EXTENDED RANGE OF HEARING,

20:22.588 --> 20:26.192
ALLOWING THEM TO PICK UP
ON THE SUBTLEST OF SOUNDS.

20:26.192 --> 20:28.661
THEIR SENSE OF SMELL
IS ALSO HEIGHTENED,

20:28.661 --> 20:31.397
100 TIMES STRONGER
THAN OUR OWN.

20:31.397 --> 20:36.736
BUT REMEMBER, THE ABBIES
DID NOT BEGIN LIKE THIS.

20:36.736 --> 20:39.171
THEY <i>BECAME</i> THIS.

20:39.171 --> 20:42.241
THEIR DNA IS ONLY
A HALF-PERCENT DIFFERENT

20:42.241 --> 20:45.578
THAN THE MAMMAL
THEY ORIGINATED FROM.

20:45.578 --> 20:47.246
[ ROARING IN DISTANCE ]

20:50.082 --> 20:52.251
DOES ANYONE KNOW
WHAT MAMMAL?

20:52.251 --> 20:56.522
IT'S ONE YOU'RE ALL
VERY FAMILIAR WITH.

20:59.358 --> 21:01.127
HOW ABOUT NOW?

21:01.127 --> 21:03.729
IT LOOKS LIKE US.

21:03.729 --> 21:05.464
THAT'S BECAUSE
IT ONCE WAS.

21:16.575 --> 21:20.146
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

21:22.648 --> 21:25.251
AFTER ORIENTATION,
I DIDN'T EAT FOR TWO DAYS.

21:25.251 --> 21:27.286
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:31.357 --> 21:32.992
HEY.

21:32.992 --> 21:34.393
THINGS MAKING
ANY MORE SENSE FOR YOU?

21:36.128 --> 21:37.429
NOT REALLY.

21:39.131 --> 21:42.334
NOT AT ALL.

21:42.334 --> 21:44.069
YEAH, IT TAKES SOME TIME
TO TAKE IT ALL IN.

21:44.069 --> 21:46.639
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:46.639 --> 21:51.277
IT'S NOT THAT.
IT'S JUST...BASIC LOGIC.

21:51.277 --> 21:52.611
OR ILLOGIC.

21:52.611 --> 21:55.014
I MEAN, IF...IF --
IF WHAT MRS. FISHER

21:55.014 --> 21:57.183
IS TEACHING
IS ACTUALLY TRUE

21:57.183 --> 22:00.719
AND THESE ABBIES
ACTUALLY EXIST,

22:00.719 --> 22:04.323
HOW HAVE I NEVER
HEARD OF THEM BEFORE?

22:04.323 --> 22:11.130
THEY'RE RUNNING AROUND
IN BROAD DAYLIGHT IN IDAHO.

22:11.130 --> 22:12.731
WE ARE IN IDAHO,
RIGHT?

22:12.731 --> 22:14.600
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH.

22:14.600 --> 22:17.036
WE ARE IN IDAHO.

22:17.036 --> 22:20.172
AND WHAT MRS. FISHER
IS TEACHING YOU IS TRUE.

22:20.172 --> 22:21.473
I PROMISE.

22:22.675 --> 22:25.411
BUT THEN, HOW --
BEN.

22:25.411 --> 22:26.979
IT'S ONLY LUNCH.

22:28.214 --> 22:30.049
IT WILL ALL
MAKE SENSE SOON.

22:30.049 --> 22:32.117
I PROMISE.

22:38.090 --> 22:40.593
Megan: LISTEN.

22:40.593 --> 22:44.463
I KNOW YOU'RE CONFUSED
AND LOST,

22:44.463 --> 22:46.999
BUT THE NEXT LESSON
SHOULD HELP CLEAR THINGS UP.

22:59.345 --> 23:03.315
THESE COINS
DO NOT HOLD VALUE ANYMORE,

23:03.315 --> 23:06.685
BUT THEY HOLD SOMETHING
FAR MORE IMPORTANT --

23:06.685 --> 23:08.153
ANSWERS.

23:11.023 --> 23:13.659
HERE WE GO.

23:13.659 --> 23:15.561
SEE?

23:15.561 --> 23:17.463
WHAT DID I SAY?
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

23:17.463 --> 23:21.267
BEAUTIFUL LIGHT,
A LOT OF SPACE.

23:21.267 --> 23:22.968
I THINK IT WAS BUILT
12 YEARS AGO,

23:22.968 --> 23:26.071
SO EVERYTHING
WORKS LIKE NEW,

23:26.071 --> 23:28.040
WHICH IS NICE.

23:32.678 --> 23:35.681
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WHY DON'T WE START IN THE BACK?

23:35.681 --> 23:38.984
AND WE'LL WORK OUR WAY
TO THE FRONT, OKAY?

23:45.157 --> 23:47.159
[ SIGHS ]

24:06.345 --> 24:11.750
IT'S -- IT'S OLD -- REALLY OLD.
MAYBE...ROMAN TIMES?

24:11.750 --> 24:14.219
THERE'S SOMETHING ON IT.

24:14.219 --> 24:16.388
CAN I SCRAPE IT OFF?

24:35.174 --> 24:36.542
IT'S A QUARTER.

24:36.542 --> 24:38.110
HMM.

24:38.110 --> 24:39.678
HOW OLD IS IT?

24:39.678 --> 24:41.547
YOU TELL ME.

24:46.352 --> 24:48.087
2095.

24:48.087 --> 24:50.589
I DON'T --
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

24:50.589 --> 24:52.391
HOW'S THAT POSSIBLE?

24:52.391 --> 24:56.261
DON'T THINK OF IT IN TERMS
OF WHAT IS OR IS NOT POSSIBLE.

24:56.261 --> 25:01.000
BEN, THINK ABOUT IT
IN TERMS OF THE FACTS.

25:01.000 --> 25:03.402
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT WHERE YOU ARE?

25:03.402 --> 25:06.105
W-WE'RE IN WAYWARD PINES
IN IDAHO.

25:06.105 --> 25:07.339
YES.

25:07.339 --> 25:09.475
BUT WHAT'S THE LAST THING
YOU REMEMBER

25:09.475 --> 25:12.211
BEFORE ARRIVING
IN WAYWARD PINES?

25:12.211 --> 25:14.046
THE ACCIDENT.
THE ACCIDENT.

25:14.046 --> 25:17.149
AND HOW ABOUT YOU,
CARRIE?

25:17.149 --> 25:19.518
A HIT-AND-RUN.

25:19.518 --> 25:20.753
AND REED?

25:20.753 --> 25:22.388
CAR CRASH.

25:25.224 --> 25:27.526
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

25:35.100 --> 25:38.637
AND WHAT DO YOU REMEMBER
AFTER THAT,

25:38.637 --> 25:41.106
AFTER YOUR ACCIDENTS.

25:41.106 --> 25:43.976
I WOKE UP IN
THE WAYWARD PINES HOSPITAL.

25:43.976 --> 25:46.345
UH...ME, TOO.

25:46.345 --> 25:48.380
ME, TOO.

25:48.380 --> 25:52.317
DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG
YOU WERE UNCONSCIOUS?

25:52.317 --> 25:57.723
YOU PROBABLY ASSUMED IT WAS ONLY
A FEW HOURS, A DAY AT MOST,

25:57.723 --> 26:00.559
BUT THIS WAS NOT THE CASE.

26:00.559 --> 26:06.165
YOUR ACCIDENTS WERE, IN FACT,
NOT ACCIDENTS AT ALL.

26:06.165 --> 26:09.968
RATHER, YOU WERE ALL...

26:09.968 --> 26:13.005
CHOSEN TO BE HERE.

26:15.541 --> 26:19.978
YOU WERE CHOSEN TO BE PART
OF A SPECIAL COMMUNITY,

26:19.978 --> 26:25.150
A COMMUNITY THAT IS NOT PART
OF THE WORLD YOU ONCE KNEW

26:25.150 --> 26:30.689
BUT RATHER
A VERY DIFFERENT WORLD,

26:30.689 --> 26:34.226
A WORLD WHERE ABBIES
THRIVE, RULE.

26:34.226 --> 26:37.596
BUT HUMAN BEINGS DID NOT
BECOME ABBIES OVERNIGHT.

26:37.596 --> 26:40.432
IT TOOK A LONG TIME,
A VERY LONG TIME.

26:40.432 --> 26:45.137
THOSE QUARTERS YOU NOW HOLD
IN YOUR HAND LOOK VERY OLD

26:45.137 --> 26:48.373
BECAUSE THEY ARE VERY OLD.

26:51.276 --> 26:58.016
THEY ARE THE LAST KNOWN RELICS
OF HUMAN CIVILIZATION --

26:58.016 --> 27:01.453
A CIVILIZATION
THAT DIED OUT...

27:01.453 --> 27:04.323
ALMOST 2,000 YEARS AGO.

27:06.625 --> 27:09.361
THIS IS NOT
THE YEAR 2014.

27:11.296 --> 27:14.600
THIS IS THE YEAR 4028.

27:23.108 --> 27:24.676
[ BEEP ]

27:24.676 --> 27:28.046
LOOK AT THAT.
IT WORKS.

27:28.046 --> 27:29.047
WHAT?

27:30.315 --> 27:33.719
There are cameras
and microphones in this house,

27:33.719 --> 27:36.155
and I need you
to keep your voice down.

27:36.155 --> 27:38.257
We can talk in here,
but we can't stay long

27:38.257 --> 27:40.292
because they will know
something's wrong.

27:40.292 --> 27:42.161
WHO? WHO?
WHO WILL KNOW?

27:42.161 --> 27:43.662
That is what I need
to know from you.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.330
You said
you saw something.

27:45.330 --> 27:51.069
I -- I WOKE UP
AFTER THE ACCIDENT, BUT...

27:51.069 --> 27:53.372
I DON'T REMEMBER MUCH.
I MUST HAVE BEEN DRUGGED.

27:54.573 --> 27:56.475
Megan:
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

27:56.475 --> 28:01.213
"THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.
HOW COULD IT BE 4028?

28:01.213 --> 28:04.149
HOW COULD WE HAVE SKIPPED
SO MUCH TIME?"

28:04.149 --> 28:05.584
[ PROJECTOR CLICKS ]

28:05.584 --> 28:10.422
BUT WHAT IF I TOLD YOU
THAT THIS MOUSE

28:10.422 --> 28:15.394
CAN GO INTO A STATE WHICH ALLOWS
IT TO SURVIVE ALL WINTER LONG

28:15.394 --> 28:17.396
WITHOUT EATING,
WITHOUT DRINKING,

28:17.396 --> 28:21.333
AND THAT IT ACTUALLY
LIVES LONGER AS A RESULT?

28:21.333 --> 28:23.235
WOULD YOU SAY
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE, TOO?

28:23.235 --> 28:25.070
BECAUSE IT'S NOT.

28:25.070 --> 28:29.041
I REMEMBER
LOOKING OUT OF...

28:29.041 --> 28:31.343
GLASS.

28:31.343 --> 28:33.345
GLASS LIKE A --
A-A WINDOW.

28:33.345 --> 28:34.580
A WINDOW, OKAY.

28:34.580 --> 28:36.081
SO, WERE YOU
IN A CAR, OR...?

28:36.081 --> 28:39.351
NO, I WAS, UH...
I WAS STANDING.

28:39.351 --> 28:42.120
AND THE WINDOW,
IT WAS SMALLER.

28:42.120 --> 28:45.224
IT WAS MORE LIKE...

28:45.224 --> 28:47.292
IT WAS --
IT WAS MORE LIKE THIS.

28:50.229 --> 28:51.663
AFTER YOUR ACCIDENTS,

28:51.663 --> 28:55.267
YOU WERE ALL PLACED
INTO HIBERNATION CHAMBERS,

28:55.267 --> 28:56.501
AND THERE YOU SLEPT.

28:56.501 --> 29:00.372
THERE WERE PEOPLE.
THEY WERE OUTSIDE.

29:00.372 --> 29:04.376
AND THEY WERE LOOKING IN.
THEY WERE L-LOOKING AT ME.

29:04.376 --> 29:06.111
DO YOU REMEMBER
ANY FACES?

29:06.111 --> 29:10.382
JUST THE -- THE --
THE NURSE.

29:10.382 --> 29:13.418
AND JUST SHADOWS AND --
AND -- AND VOICES,

29:13.418 --> 29:15.153
AND THEN I --
I PASSED OUT.

29:15.153 --> 29:16.622
AND AS SOON AS YOU AWOKE,

29:16.622 --> 29:20.292
YOU BECAME PART OF...

29:20.292 --> 29:22.461
[ SIGHS ]

29:22.461 --> 29:24.129
THE FIRST GENERATION.

29:25.697 --> 29:27.099
BUT THERE WERE
MORE OF THESE.

29:27.099 --> 29:28.300
THERE WERE MORE OF THESE --
THESE, UH --

29:28.300 --> 29:31.370
THESE CHAMBERS,
AND THEY WERE ALL...

29:32.504 --> 29:37.376
THEY WERE ALL
FILLED WITH...

29:37.376 --> 29:38.343
FILLED WITH WHAT?

29:38.343 --> 29:41.280
WITH PEOPLE.

29:41.280 --> 29:44.182
WHY -- WHY WERE
<i>WE</i> CHOSEN?

29:44.182 --> 29:47.252
THAT'S THE LAST QUESTION,
ISN'T IT?

29:47.252 --> 29:49.755
AND PERHAPS
THE MOST IMPORTANT.

29:49.755 --> 29:52.658
DO YOU BELIEVE ME?

29:52.658 --> 29:54.393
YES, I BELIEVE YOU.

29:54.393 --> 29:56.395
[ SIGHS ]

29:56.395 --> 29:57.663
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT IS IT?

29:57.663 --> 29:59.197
WHAT -- WHAT --
WHAT IS THIS PLACE?

29:59.197 --> 30:00.999
THE SIMPLE ANSWER IS,

30:00.999 --> 30:06.471
YOU WERE CHOSEN TO ASSURE
THE SURVIVAL OF THE HUMAN RACE.

30:09.541 --> 30:12.444
I AM GOING TO
FIGURE THIS OUT.

30:12.444 --> 30:14.479
I WILL FIND OUT
WHAT IT IS THAT YOU SAW

30:14.479 --> 30:15.747
AND WHY WE ARE HERE --
I WILL.

30:15.747 --> 30:18.050
BUT I NEED YOU
TO TAKE THIS HOUSE,

30:18.050 --> 30:20.752
AND I NEED YOU TO DO IT
WITH A SMILE ON YOUR FACE, OKAY?

30:23.522 --> 30:26.558
[ SIGHS ]
SO, I THINK THAT'S IT.

30:26.558 --> 30:30.162
AND REMEMBER, EVERYTHING
THAT YOU SEE HERE IS YOURS.

30:30.162 --> 30:31.630
YOU GET TO KEEP IT.

30:31.630 --> 30:34.232
AND THE BEST PART IS,
IS IT DOESN'T EVEN COST A PENNY.

30:34.232 --> 30:37.302
SO, YOU JUST GET TO MOVE IN
AND START LIVING YOUR LIFE.

30:37.302 --> 30:41.106
DOESN'T THAT SOUND GREAT?
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

30:43.008 --> 30:44.543
UH...

30:44.543 --> 30:46.011
THANK YOU.
MY PLEASURE.

30:51.350 --> 30:54.653
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

30:57.122 --> 30:58.657
[ HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING ]

31:18.377 --> 31:21.747
Megan:
OVER 2,000 YEARS AGO,

31:21.747 --> 31:25.517
A GREAT SCIENTIST FORESAW
THE COMING OF THE ABERRATIONS.

31:25.517 --> 31:28.420
THE PERFECT EQUATION
THAT HELD OUR PLANET TOGETHER

31:28.420 --> 31:30.122
WAS UNRAVELING,

31:30.122 --> 31:33.291
AND HE KNEW MOTHER NATURE
WOULD DO AS SHE ALWAYS DOES --

31:33.291 --> 31:35.227
SHE WOULD EVOLVE,

31:35.227 --> 31:38.663
SHE WOULD CHANGE THE EQUATION,

31:38.663 --> 31:43.235
SHE WOULD CHANGE US.

31:43.235 --> 31:46.638
THIS SCIENTIST WANTED TO SAVE
A SELECT SAMPLE OF HUMANS

31:46.638 --> 31:48.039
FROM THIS CHANGE

31:48.039 --> 31:52.611
TO PRESERVE OUR KIND
AS WE ONCE WERE.

31:52.611 --> 31:56.615
SO HE CREATED AN ARK.

31:56.615 --> 31:59.684
HE CREATED WAYWARD PINES.

32:15.567 --> 32:18.136
A SCIENTIST?

32:18.136 --> 32:20.572
HIS NAME
IS DAVID PILCHER.

32:20.572 --> 32:23.975
UNFORTUNATELY, YOU WILL
NEVER MEET DAVID PILCHER,

32:23.975 --> 32:25.410
BUT YOU CAN TAKE COMFORT

32:25.410 --> 32:30.248
IN THE FACT THAT
HE IS ALWAYS WATCHING OVER YOU.

32:30.248 --> 32:34.019
HE WILL NEVER ALLOW
ANYTHING TO HAPPEN TO YOU

32:34.019 --> 32:37.022
BECAUSE YOU
<i>ARE</i> THE FUTURE.

32:37.022 --> 32:42.027
YOU ARE
THE FIRST GENERATION,

32:42.027 --> 32:45.597
AND HE IS YOUR PROTECTOR.

32:54.673 --> 32:57.676
YOU NEVER CEASE
TO IMPRESS ME, ETHAN.

32:59.411 --> 33:01.346
NO ONE HAS EVER
MADE IT OUT THIS FAR BEFORE,

33:01.346 --> 33:02.447
NOT ON THEIR OWN.

33:05.050 --> 33:07.486
I SHOULD INTRODUCE MYSELF.

33:08.720 --> 33:10.722
DAVID PILCHER.

33:15.994 --> 33:16.695
PILCHER.

33:20.031 --> 33:22.200
TELL ME ABOUT
THIS GUY PILCHER.

33:22.200 --> 33:25.136
MY NAME IS DR. JENKINS.
DO YOU KNOW WHERE YOU ARE?

33:25.136 --> 33:27.305
HAVE YOU NOTICED ANYTHING ELSE
GO UNEXPLAINED?

33:29.040 --> 33:30.709
SO,
YOU'RE DAVID PILCHER.

33:32.444 --> 33:34.279
WE CAN'T STAY HERE.

33:34.279 --> 33:37.649
COME WITH ME,
BACK TO WAYWARD PINES.

33:37.649 --> 33:38.683
PILCHER!
[ RIFLE COCKS ]

33:40.385 --> 33:41.486
PUT DOWN YOUR WEAPON.

33:41.486 --> 33:43.555
PUT IT DOWN.

33:46.725 --> 33:49.728
WHAT IS THIS?
SOME KIND OF AN EXPERIMENT?

33:51.363 --> 33:53.765
THAT'S NOT BOISE, OKAY?

33:53.765 --> 33:55.233
I KNOW BOISE.

33:55.233 --> 33:58.470
YOUR MIND IS LASHING OUT,
ETHAN.

33:58.470 --> 34:00.338
IT DOESN'T WANT TO ACCEPT
THE TRUTH,

34:00.338 --> 34:02.607
BUT TRUST YOUR OWN EYES,

34:02.607 --> 34:06.111
EVERYTHING
YOU'VE SEEN TODAY.

34:06.111 --> 34:07.746
THERE'S NOTHING FOR YOU
OUT HERE.

34:07.746 --> 34:12.984
THE WORLD YOU KNOW
IS GONE.

34:12.984 --> 34:16.354
AND OUR SPECIES HAS EVOLVED
INTO SOMETHING LESS THAN HUMAN.

34:16.354 --> 34:18.490
ALL THAT IS LEFT
OF CIVILIZATION,

34:18.490 --> 34:24.095
ALL THAT REMAINS IS...
WAYWARD PINES.

34:24.095 --> 34:26.231
WHAT DO YOU WANT
FROM ME?

34:26.231 --> 34:28.667
I WANT YOU
TO COME WITH ME.

34:28.667 --> 34:30.635
AND I'LL SHOW YOU HOW,
TOGETHER,

34:30.635 --> 34:32.737
WE CAN CHANGE THINGS
FOR THE BETTER.

34:32.737 --> 34:34.005
[ SCREECHING IN DISTANCE ]

34:38.276 --> 34:39.744
OR IF YOU PREFER,

34:39.744 --> 34:43.281
YOU CAN DISCOVER FOR YOURSELF
WHAT IS OUT HERE.

34:43.281 --> 34:45.617
[ SIGHS ]

34:45.617 --> 34:49.054
IT'S YOUR CHOICE,
ETHAN.

34:49.054 --> 34:53.525
Megan: WHAT YOU LEARN TODAY IS
FOR YOUR EYES AND EARS ONLY.

34:53.525 --> 34:55.627
YOU DO NOT TELL
YOUR PARENTS.

34:55.627 --> 34:59.631
YOU DO NOT TELL ANY ADULTS
FOR ONE SIMPLE REASON.

35:01.466 --> 35:07.439
THE FUTURE
OF THIS GREAT TOWN LIES

35:07.439 --> 35:09.441
NOT WITH THE ADULTS...

35:12.510 --> 35:14.646
...BUT WITH YOU.

35:14.646 --> 35:18.683
NOW, YOU MAY THINK
WHAT I'M ASKING IS UNFAIR.

35:18.683 --> 35:23.421
YOU MAY FEEL LIKE
YOUR PARENTS DESERVE TO KNOW.

35:23.421 --> 35:25.023
SO DID CHRIS.

35:26.558 --> 35:29.294
CHRIS WAS A STUDENT,
JUST LIKE YOU.

35:29.294 --> 35:30.662
HE SAT IN THIS VERY ROOM,

35:30.662 --> 35:33.398
AND HE SAW AND HEARD
THE VERY SAME THINGS

35:33.398 --> 35:38.036
THAT YOU DID TODAY,
AND IT SCARED HIM.

35:38.036 --> 35:41.106
WHEN HE WENT HOME,
HE TOLD HIS PARENTS EVERYTHING.

35:41.106 --> 35:47.679
THE NEXT DAY, CHRIS' PARENTS
DECIDED TO GO ON A TRIP.

35:47.679 --> 35:54.019
BEFORE THEY LEFT,
HIS DAD CLOSED THE GARAGE DOOR.

35:54.019 --> 35:57.522
HIS MOM CONNECTED
THE GARDEN HOSE

35:57.522 --> 36:02.293
FROM THE TAILPIPE
TO THE WINDOW.

36:02.293 --> 36:06.698
HIS DAD TURNED THE KEY.

36:06.698 --> 36:11.269
AND 15 MINUTES LATER...

36:11.269 --> 36:13.238
THEY WERE ALL DEAD.

36:17.075 --> 36:19.377
THE REALITY IS

36:19.377 --> 36:23.348
YOUR PARENTS HAVE LIVED TOO LONG
IN THE OLD WORLD.

36:23.348 --> 36:26.985
THE TRUTH IS TOO MUCH
FOR THEIR MINDS.

36:26.985 --> 36:30.221
TELLING THEM WOULD NOT ONLY
PUT THEIR LIVES IN DANGER

36:30.221 --> 36:35.226
AND NOT JUST YOUR OWN
BUT ALL OF WAYWARD PINES.

36:35.226 --> 36:37.262
[ BELL JINGLES ]

37:04.389 --> 37:07.525
DAVID PILCHER FORESAW
A GREAT FLOOD,

37:07.525 --> 37:10.261
AND HE BUILT AN ARK,

37:10.261 --> 37:14.666
AND HE FILLED THIS ARK
WITH PEOPLE LIKE YOU AND ME.

37:14.666 --> 37:19.604
PEOPLE HE DEEMED NECESSARY
FOR THE SURVIVAL OF MANKIND.

37:19.604 --> 37:24.142
WE ARE THE LUCKY ONES,
THE CHOSEN FEW.

37:24.142 --> 37:30.248
BUT THIS ARK WILL ONLY SURVIVE
IF WE ALL FOLLOW THE RULES.

37:30.248 --> 37:34.252
IF THERE IS ONE HOLE,
ONE CRACK,

37:34.252 --> 37:39.157
THEN THE WATER WILL GET IN,
AND WE WILL ALL DROWN.

37:39.157 --> 37:41.559
IT'S UP TO YOU TO MAKE SURE
THAT DOESN'T HAPPEN.

37:41.559 --> 37:46.431
IT'S UP TO YOU
TO STEER THE ARK SAFELY TO SHORE

37:46.431 --> 37:49.033
BECAUSE YOU ARE...

37:49.033 --> 37:50.502
All:
THE FIRST GENERATION.

37:50.502 --> 37:52.403
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T CATCH THAT.

37:52.403 --> 37:54.038
THE FIRST GENERATION!

37:54.038 --> 37:56.374
I'M SORRY?

37:56.374 --> 37:59.511
THE FIRST GENERATION!!

37:59.511 --> 38:00.645
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

38:06.217 --> 38:07.385
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

38:07.385 --> 38:09.454
Bill: I THINK I OWE SOMEONE
A GOLD STAR.

38:09.454 --> 38:12.757
[ WHISTLING ]

38:12.757 --> 38:14.425
OH, I DIDN'T THINK YOU WERE
SERIOUS ABOUT THE GOLD STAR.

38:14.425 --> 38:16.461
[ LAUGHS ]

38:16.461 --> 38:18.997
I'M ALWAYS SERIOUS.

38:18.997 --> 38:21.065
AND MY GUESS...

38:21.065 --> 38:26.204
IS IT WON'T BE
THE LAST STAR THIS WEEK.

38:26.204 --> 38:27.639
YOU'RE UP TO BAT AGAIN.

38:31.309 --> 38:34.045
HOW OFTEN WOULD YOU SAY
PEOPLE MOVE TO WAYWARD PINES,

38:34.045 --> 38:36.381
JUST AVERAGE?
I DON'T KNOW.

38:36.381 --> 38:39.717
A COUPLE TRICKLE IN
EVERY MONTH OR SO, I GUESS.

38:39.717 --> 38:41.586
PRETTY STEADY,
NOW THAT I THINK ABOUT IT,

38:41.586 --> 38:43.421
LIKE CLOCKWORK.

38:43.421 --> 38:47.559
THE MINUTE YOU NEED SOMEONE,
THEY JUST SHOW UP.

38:47.559 --> 38:49.694
AND IS IT ALWAYS
AFTER AN ACCIDENT?

38:49.694 --> 38:51.296
I'M SORRY?

38:51.296 --> 38:53.765
I NOTICED THAT PEOPLE MOVING
TO WAYWARD PINES,

38:53.765 --> 38:55.333
THEY'RE ALL
IN CAR ACCIDENTS.

38:55.333 --> 38:58.703
I FIND THAT STRANGE,
DON'T YOU?

38:58.703 --> 39:02.073
MY ADVICE...

39:02.073 --> 39:04.242
IS DON'T THINK TOO HARD,
SWEETIE.

39:04.242 --> 39:06.978
IT'S NOT VERY BECOMING,

39:06.978 --> 39:09.180
AND I'D HATE FOR
SOMETHING TO HAPPEN
TO THAT PRETTY LITTLE FACE.

39:15.086 --> 39:16.354
Megan: BIG SMILE.

39:17.255 --> 39:19.357
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

39:19.357 --> 39:20.658
[ SIGHS ]

39:20.658 --> 39:22.994
NOW, IF YOU WILL
ALL PLEASE FOLLOW ME.

40:25.156 --> 40:27.725
WELCOME
TO THE FIRST GENERATION.

40:27.725 --> 40:30.595
[ RHYTHMIC THUDDING ]

40:34.065 --> 40:36.167
[ TEMPO INCREASES ]

41:06.331 --> 41:09.600
Dr. Jenkins: I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE FEELING, ETHAN.

41:09.600 --> 41:12.603
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

41:12.603 --> 41:16.140
AT FIRST, IT'S --
IT'S THE PERSONAL THINGS.

41:16.140 --> 41:20.278
THE FAMILY
YOU'LL NEVER SEE AGAIN,

41:20.278 --> 41:22.413
YOUR FRIENDS.

41:22.413 --> 41:24.349
THE BOSS
YOU THOUGHT YOU HATED.

41:24.349 --> 41:27.185
AND THEN...

41:27.185 --> 41:31.222
YOUR MIND STARTS
THINKING BIGGER.

41:31.222 --> 41:34.459
ABOUT ALL
THE LOST CULTURE --

41:34.459 --> 41:38.763
LANGUAGES, ART,
KNOWLEDGE.

41:38.763 --> 41:46.738
THOUSANDS OF YEARS OF CULTURE
ALL GONE IN AN INSTANT.

41:46.738 --> 41:52.110
AND YOU START TO THINK,
"IS THIS REALLY IT?

41:52.110 --> 41:55.113
"THE LAST OF MANKIND?

41:55.113 --> 41:57.348
DO I EVEN
WANT TO BE HERE?"

41:57.348 --> 42:00.485
BUT SLOWLY, SLOWLY,

42:00.485 --> 42:04.655
YOU REALIZE
EVERYTHING YOU STILL HAVE,

42:04.655 --> 42:06.491
A NEW COMMUNITY...

42:06.491 --> 42:08.493
[ LAUGHTER ]

42:08.493 --> 42:10.261
...A FAMILY...

42:12.730 --> 42:14.766
...A FUTURE.

42:16.601 --> 42:21.639
YOU STILL HAVE
WAYWARD PINES.

42:24.042 --> 42:26.711
BUT WHAT IS
WAYWARD PINES?

42:26.711 --> 42:29.480
COME WITH ME,
AND I'LL SHOW YOU.

42:29.480 --> 42:31.549
[ SCREECHING IN DISTANCE ]

42:33.518 --> 42:34.619
WE HAVE TO GO.

42:34.619 --> 42:36.087
NOW!

42:38.489 --> 42:39.624
[ HELICOPTER ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

42:39.624 --> 42:41.092
[ SCREECHING CONTINUES ]

42:41.092 --> 42:43.327
LOOKS LIKE
YOU COULD USE A NURSE.

42:43.327 --> 42:44.595
[ HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING ]

42:44.595 --> 42:46.364
COME ON.

42:47.698 --> 42:49.267
GO, GO, GO!

42:49.267 --> 42:50.601
[ SCREECHING ]
